## Tradeoff (stated to user)
Deliberate duplication of the digest impl (client weave.trace.digest vs server
weave.shared.digest). Violates DRY on purpose: independence is the goal; the
conformance corpus is the safety net that makes the duplication safe (drift fails
tests/contract).

## Hints for Future Agents
- weave.shared.digest is now effectively SERVER-owned (server + the fixture
  generator use it); it moves to core with the server. weave.trace.digest is the
  client's and stays.
- The import-linter contract uses allow_indirect_imports=true, so it catches only
  DIRECT 'from weave.shared.digest import'. The client still transitively loads
  weave.shared.digest at runtime via weave.shared.__init__'s re-export; fully
  severing that is a deeper follow-up (don't eagerly re-export digest from
  weave.shared.__init__) but is not required for the decoupling guarantee.
